The paper deals with the fundamental graph coloring problem and its maximization version, which are classic topics in computer science. The use of semidefinite programming and the 2-to-1 conjecture suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The study of graph coloring also has connections to computational geometry (cs.CG), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG), which makes these sub-categories likely as well.
